cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for training deep latent variable models of discrete structures, specifically text sequences. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which encompasses topics related to representation learning and generative models. The paper also involves natural language processing, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the authors mention the use of the method for image data, which could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves the use of adversarial training, which is a common technique in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
